<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-04-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="482" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-04-20"><hi rend="italic">April 20,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 689.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 1713, of the 5th instant, reporting that as an evidence of their
                            appreciation of the good offices exercised by you in their behalf a
                            delegation of Syrians <pb facs="0659" n="539" xml:id="pg_539"/> had
                            extended to you and to the officers of the <hi rend="italic">Brooklyn</hi> an invitation to attend a reception, which invitation
                            was declined both by you and by the officers of the <hi rend="italic">Brooklyn.</hi></p>
                        <p>The Department approves your action in declining to attend such a
                            reception.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">F. B. Loomis.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>